Program: Free Thinking
Title: Cutting Tradition
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03g2yj1
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 27 Aug 2014
What do recent debates among medical ethicists and lawyers over male infant circumcision reveal about the different ways we view male and female bodies? Rebecca Steinfeld, from the School of Oriental and African Studies at the University of London, looks at changing attitudes to religious traditions involving genital cutting. Producer: Zahid Warley First broadcast in November 2013. Show less